Usage:
  cape submission new <scenario> <language> <version> <github-handle> [variant]

Required Arguments:
  <scenario>          Benchmark name (must exist in scenarios/)
  <language>          Compiler/language name (letters/digits/hyphens only)
  <version>           Compiler version (e.g., 1.52.0.0 or 1.1.17)
  <github-handle>     Your GitHub handle (1-39 chars, alphanumeric and hyphens)

Optional Arguments:
  [variant]           Optional variant identifier (e.g., 'memoized', 'iterative', 'pfix')
                      Use when submitting multiple optimization approaches for same scenario
                      Lowercase letters, digits, and hyphens only

Examples:
  # Generic/default implementation
  cape submission new fibonacci Plinth 1.53.0 Unisay

  # Prescribed algorithm scenario (use scenario-specific directory)
  cape submission new fibonacci_naive_recursion Plinth 1.53.0 Unisay

  # Open optimization with specific variant
  cape submission new fibonacci Plutarch 1.11.1 SeungheonOh memoized
  cape submission new factorial Plutarch 1.11.1 SeungheonOh pfix

Directory Naming:
  - Generic: <language>_<version>_<github-handle>
  - With variant: <language>_<version>_<github-handle>_<variant>

Notes:
  - Scenario must exist in scenarios/<scenario>/
  - Variant is optional; use only when submitting multiple optimization approaches
  - For prescribed algorithm benchmarks, use scenario-specific directories
    (e.g., fibonacci_naive_recursion, factorial_naive_recursion)
  - GitHub handle rules: 1-39 chars, alphanumeric and hyphens, cannot start/end with '-'
